{"id":"521aa492-50bf-4402-acb6-d407f1ae8098","type":"SprintAdded","timestamp":1776847582319,"actor":"ui","projectId":"proj_1776847192658_clz2mby18","data":{"id":"sprint_1776847582318_1","name":"Sprint 1: Project Scaffolding & Claude SDK Setup","description":"Initialize the project (Node.js/TypeScript), install the Anthropic SDK, configure environment variables for the API key, and create a minimal data layer with hardcoded sample prompts/tools and a simple conversation state module to feed the managed agent.","priority":"high","status":"pending"},"prevHash":"d7a4421d14fc86bc64e7fe0f4f0377bc2c46876819e2692dbb7d67893c6bdd5a"}
{"id":"2302f4bf-8057-472c-a93c-6911966edc44","type":"SprintAdded","timestamp":1776847582321,"actor":"ui","projectId":"proj_1776847192658_clz2mby18","data":{"id":"sprint_1776847582318_2","name":"Sprint 2: Managed Agent Core Loop & CLI Interface","description":"Implement the bare-bones managed agent following the quickstart docs — wire up a single agent invocation with one example tool, run the agent loop end-to-end, and expose it through a simple CLI that accepts a user prompt and prints the agent response.","priority":"high","status":"pending"},"prevHash":"b85e99a8a27750bbf0903cfa281025a2777431455dd03af7c3304c4587ccfab0"}
{"id":"177eef83-54f8-4566-b1e9-e6b449048453","type":"TasksGenerated","timestamp":1776847614647,"actor":"ui","projectId":"proj_1776847192658_clz2mby18","data":{"sprintId":"sprint_1776847582318_1","tasks":[{"id":"9f94fc84-9a11-4b2e-aac8-fa2eed24feae","title":"Initialize Node.js/TypeScript project with Anthropic SDK","description":"Run `npm init -y` and install dependencies: `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, `dotenv`, `typescript`, `ts-node`, `@types/node`. Create `tsconfig.json` targeting ES2022 with CommonJS modules, `src/` as rootDir, and `dist/` as outDir. Add npm scripts for `build`, `start`, and `dev` (ts-node entrypoint). Create `.gitignore` to exclude `node_modules`, `dist`, and `.env`.","purpose":"Establishes the runtime, type-checking, and dependency foundation required to run the Anthropic SDK quickstart example.","functionality":"A working Node.js/TypeScript project skeleton with the Anthropic SDK installed and ready to import.","successCriteria":["`package.json` lists `@anthropic-ai/sdk` and `dotenv` as dependencies","`tsconfig.json` compiles files under `src/` without errors","`npm run build` produces output in `dist/`","`.gitignore` excludes `node_modules`, `dist`, and `.env`"],"status":"pending","priority":"critical","relevantFiles":[{"path":"package.json","action":"create"},{"path":"tsconfig.json","action":"create"},{"path":".gitignore","action":"create"}]},{"id":"a4e3dd61-f886-4670-806b-9a9917645525","title":"Configure environment variables and Anthropic client module","description":"Create `.env.example` with `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=` placeholder and a local `.env` loaded via `dotenv`. Create `src/config/env.ts` that reads and validates `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` on startup. Create `src/config/anthropic.ts` that exports a singleton `Anthropic` client instance initialized from the env module.","purpose":"Centralizes API key configuration and provides a single reusable Anthropic client for the agent loop in Sprint 2.","functionality":"Loads the API key from `.env` at startup and exposes a ready-to-use Anthropic SDK client.","successCriteria":["`src/config/env.ts` throws a clear error if `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is missing","`src/config/anthropic.ts` exports a configured `Anthropic` client instance","`.env.example` documents the required `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` variable","Importing the client module does not crash when the env var is set"],"status":"pending","priority":"critical","relevantFiles":[{"path":".env.example","action":"create"},{"path":"src/config/env.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"src/config/anthropic.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"package.json","action":"read"}]},{"id":"4ea932d8-0a70-4419-8b26-2ea0cd311ec4","title":"Create hardcoded sample prompts and system instructions","description":"Create `src/data/prompts.ts` exporting a `SYSTEM_PROMPT` constant (brief instructions for a helpful assistant that can use tools) and a `SAMPLE_USER_PROMPTS` array with 2-3 example prompts suitable for demoing the managed agent (e.g., weather lookup, simple calculation). Export typed constants only — no runtime logic.","purpose":"Provides deterministic, reusable prompt content so the Sprint 2 CLI can demo the agent without requiring user input for every run.","functionality":"Static prompt data module supplying system and user prompts to the agent loop.","successCriteria":["`SYSTEM_PROMPT` is exported as a non-empty string constant","`SAMPLE_USER_PROMPTS` contains at least 2 entries","Module has no runtime side effects on import","Types are explicitly declared (e.g., `readonly string[]`)"],"status":"pending","priority":"high","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/data/prompts.ts","action":"create"}]},{"id":"d8d2b34a-8055-4be9-a344-e81bc38011f0","title":"Define sample tool schemas for the managed agent","description":"Create `src/data/tools.ts` exporting a `TOOLS` array conforming to the Anthropic SDK `Tool` type, containing one example tool definition (e.g., `get_weather` with `location` string input) following the quickstart format. Also create `src/data/toolHandlers.ts` with a stubbed handler map that returns hardcoded mock results keyed by tool name. Do not implement real external API calls.","purpose":"Supplies the tool definitions and mock handlers that Sprint 2's agent loop will pass to the Anthropic API and invoke on tool_use blocks.","functionality":"Static tool schema definitions plus a lookup of stub handler functions returning canned responses.","successCriteria":["`TOOLS` array contains at least one tool with `name`, `description`, and `input_schema`","Tool `input_schema` is a valid JSON Schema object","`toolHandlers.ts` exports a handler map keyed by tool name returning stringified mock results","Handler for the defined tool returns deterministic output when called"],"status":"pending","priority":"high","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/data/tools.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"src/data/toolHandlers.ts","action":"create"}]},{"id":"c92e31b3-d198-4d3f-af05-0235f41630da","title":"Implement conversation state module","description":"Create `src/data/conversationState.ts` exporting a `ConversationState` class (or factory) that maintains an in-memory array of `MessageParam` objects. Expose `addUserMessage(text)`, `addAssistantMessage(content)`, `addToolResult(toolUseId, result)`, `getMessages()`, and `reset()` methods. Use types from `@anthropic-ai/sdk` so messages plug directly into `client.messages.create`.","purpose":"Provides the message history buffer the Sprint 2 agent loop mutates across turns to support multi-turn tool_use → tool_result cycles.","functionality":"In-memory conversation log that accumulates user, assistant, and tool-result messages in the shape required by the Messages API.","successCriteria":["`ConversationState` exposes add/get/reset methods","`getMessages()` returns an array typed as `MessageParam[]` from the Anthropic SDK","`addToolResult` produces a user message with a `tool_result` content block referencing the given `tool_use_id`","`reset()` clears the internal message array"],"status":"pending","priority":"high","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/data/conversationState.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"package.json","action":"read"}]}]},"prevHash":"dd22c39a19dcabe39a29d1a98606c11cfc2d9b8d4e498cce7f995d6da77bdf32"}
{"id":"8c96bae9-a9db-4616-a235-379fa1f07d05","type":"TasksGenerated","timestamp":1776847645886,"actor":"ui","projectId":"proj_1776847192658_clz2mby18","data":{"sprintId":"sprint_1776847582318_2","tasks":[{"id":"860e7092-676c-48c9-93a3-eda835dab10c","title":"Implement tool dispatcher for agent tool_use blocks","description":"Create `src/agent/toolDispatcher.ts` exporting a `dispatchTool(name, input)` function that looks up the handler in `src/data/toolHandlers.ts` and invokes it with the provided input, returning a string result. Handle the happy path only — assume the tool name exists in the handler map. This bridges the agent loop's `tool_use` content blocks to the Sprint 1 mock handlers.","purpose":"Provides the execution layer that converts Anthropic SDK tool_use requests into concrete handler invocations during the agent loop.","functionality":"Routes a tool name and input object to the matching handler and returns its stringified result for inclusion in a tool_result message.","successCriteria":["`dispatchTool` returns the mock result string for the sample tool defined in Sprint 1","Function accepts `(name: string, input: Record<string, unknown>)` and returns `string`","Module imports handlers from `src/data/toolHandlers.ts`"],"status":"pending","priority":"high","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/agent/toolDispatcher.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"src/data/toolHandlers.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/data/tools.ts","action":"read"}]},{"id":"e515c36d-af99-466d-a68a-77af2a07d2d8","title":"Implement managed agent loop with Anthropic Messages API","description":"Create `src/agent/runAgent.ts` exporting `runAgent(userPrompt: string): Promise<string>`. Instantiate a `ConversationState`, seed it with the user prompt, then enter a while loop that calls `client.messages.create` with the system prompt, `TOOLS`, and current messages. On `stop_reason === 'tool_use'`, dispatch each tool_use block via the dispatcher and append tool_result messages; on `stop_reason === 'end_turn'`, concatenate text blocks and return. Use model `claude-sonnet-4-5` with `max_tokens: 1024`.","purpose":"Implements the core quickstart agent loop that ties together the SDK client, tool definitions, handlers, and conversation state into a complete multi-turn tool-using agent.","functionality":"Runs a managed agent end-to-end: sends messages, handles tool_use by invoking handlers, loops until `end_turn`, and returns the final assistant text.","successCriteria":["`runAgent` returns a string containing the final assistant text response","Loop invokes `dispatchTool` for every `tool_use` block returned by the API","Loop terminates cleanly when the API returns `stop_reason: 'end_turn'`","Tool results are appended to conversation state with matching `tool_use_id`","Uses `SYSTEM_PROMPT` and `TOOLS` imported from the `src/data` modules"],"status":"pending","priority":"critical","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/agent/runAgent.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"src/config/anthropic.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/data/prompts.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/data/tools.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/data/conversationState.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/agent/toolDispatcher.ts","action":"read"}]},{"id":"6690d394-c4e2-4ef9-9cc5-973c42dfe7c3","title":"Create CLI entrypoint accepting a user prompt","description":"Create `src/index.ts` as the CLI entrypoint. Read the user prompt from `process.argv.slice(2).join(' ')`; if empty, fall back to the first entry in `SAMPLE_USER_PROMPTS`. Call `runAgent(prompt)` and print the returned response to stdout with `console.log`. Wire `package.json` `start` and `dev` scripts to invoke this file.","purpose":"Exposes the agent loop through a minimal command-line interface so the POC can be demonstrated with a single `npm run dev` invocation.","functionality":"Parses a prompt from CLI args (or uses a sample fallback), runs the managed agent, and prints the final response.","successCriteria":["`npm run dev \"hello\"` prints an assistant response to stdout","Running without arguments uses a prompt from `SAMPLE_USER_PROMPTS`","`package.json` `start`/`dev` scripts point at `src/index.ts`","CLI exits cleanly with code 0 on success"],"status":"pending","priority":"high","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/index.ts","action":"create"},{"path":"package.json","action":"modify"},{"path":"src/agent/runAgent.ts","action":"read"},{"path":"src/data/prompts.ts","action":"read"}]},{"id":"8f259a2a-6f02-4b89-b47a-907860446a8a","title":"Add verbose turn-by-turn logging to the agent loop","description":"Modify `src/agent/runAgent.ts` to log each iteration: print a header for every API call, log any `tool_use` blocks (name + input) before dispatch, and log the returned tool result. Keep output readable with clear section separators. This is the primary way to observe the managed agent behavior in the POC demo.","purpose":"Makes the quickstart agent loop observable from the CLI so viewers can see tool calls and results rather than only the final answer.","functionality":"Prints a trace of each agent turn — request boundary, tool_use blocks, tool_result content — to stdout during `runAgent` execution.","successCriteria":["Each API iteration prints a distinguishable turn header","Every tool_use invocation logs tool name and input","Every tool result logs the returned string","Final assistant text is clearly separated from trace output"],"status":"pending","priority":"medium","relevantFiles":[{"path":"src/agent/runAgent.ts","action":"modify"}]}]},"prevHash":"f5103e8015715a5a3f30b741b889a5b3fe8f59d19d7667da74490a79f5b6da8c"}
